=== History === {{div col}} *[[Dhimit√´r Antoni]] (1922‚Äì1995) *[[Frang Bardhi]], Frang Bardhi ([[Latin]]: ''Franciscus Blancus'', Italian: ''Francesco Bianchi'', 1606‚Äì1643) {{spaced ndash}} bishop and author of the early eras of [[Albanian literature]] *[[Marin Barleti]] (1450‚Äì1512/13) {{spaced ndash}} historian and [[Catholic]] priest from [[Shkodra]];<ref>{{cite book|last=Setton|first=Kenneth M.|title=The papacy and the Levant (1204‚Äì1571).|year=1978|publisher=Amer.philos.soc.|location=Philadelphia|isbn=978-0-87169-127-9|page=73|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0Sz2VYI0l1IC&pg=PA73|edition=null|quote= ...perhaps of Italian origin.}}</ref> considered the first Albanian historian because of his 1504 [[The Siege of Shkodra (book)|eyewitness account]] of the 1478 [[siege of Shkodra]]; better known for his second work, a biography on [[Skanderbeg]], translated into many languages in the 16th to the 20th centuries *[[Aleks Buda]] (1910‚Äì1993) {{spaced ndash}} Albanian historian of [[Jewish]] origin *[[Jorgo Bulo]] (1939‚Äì2015) {{spaced ndash}} [[philologist]], historian, and [[literary critic]]; member of the [[Albanian Academy of Arts and Sciences]] *[[Eqrem √áabej]] (1908‚Äì1980) {{spaced ndash}} historical linguist and scholar who, through the publication of numerous studies gained a reputation as a key expert in the research into [[Albanian-language]], literature, [[ethnology]] and [[linguistics]] *[[Kostandin √áekrezi]] (1892‚Äì1959) *[[Midhat Frash√´ri]] (1880‚Äì1949) *[[Naim Frash√´ri]] (1846‚Äì1900) *[[Demetrio Franco]] (1443‚Äì1525) {{spaced ndash}} scholar, soldier and [[Roman Catholicism|Catholic]] priest; known for ''Comentario de le cose de' Turchi, et del S. Georgio Scanderbeg, principe d' Epyro'', a biography of the national hero of Albania [[Skanderbeg]] *[[Ibrahim Gashi]] *[[Qemal Haxhihasani]] (1916‚Äì1991) *[[Muzafer Korkuti]] (born 1936) *[[Rexhep Krasniqi]] (1906‚Äì1999) *[[Beqir Meta]] *[[Ndoc Nikaj]] (1864‚Äì1951) {{spaced ndash}} pr