{{Infobox person | name = Ryan Maness | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | residence = | nationality = | other_names = | known_for = | education = | alma mater = [[University of Illinois at Chicago]] | employer = | occupation = Cybersecurity expert | title = | salary = | networth = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | religion = | spouse = | children = | parents = | relatives = }} '''Ryan Maness''' is an American cybersecurity expert.
==Early life== Ryan Maness received a PhD from the [[University of Illinois at Chicago]].<ref name="northeasternryanmaness">{{cite web|title=Ryan Maness|url=https://www.northeastern.edu/cssh/faculty/ryan-maness|website=Northeastern University College of Social Sciences and Humanities|accessdate=October 13, 2016}}</ref>
==Career== Maness is a Visiting Fellow in Political Science at Northeastern University.<ref name="northeasternryanmaness"/> He is the co-author of two books. In ''Cyber Wars versus Cyber Realities'', he argues that the era of cyberwar has been characterized by "restraint".<ref name="thediplomattheuschinaand">{{cite news|last1=Farley|first1=Robert|title=The US, China and an Abundance of Cyber-Caution|url=http://thediplomat.com/2015/12/the-us-china-and-an-abundance-of-cyber-caution/|accessdate=October 13, 2016|work=The Diplomat|date=December 11, 2015}}</ref> He believes that Russia will not tamper with US voter machines in the [[United States presidential election, 2016|2016 presidential election]].<ref name="wiredamericaselectronicvotingbarrett">{{cite news|last1=Barrett|first1=Brian|title=America‚Äôs Electronic Voting Machines Are Scarily Easy Targets|url=https://www.wired.com/2016/08/americas-voting-machines-arent-ready-election/|accessdate=October 13, 2016|work=Wired|date=August 2, 2016}}</ref>
Maness is a member of the [[American Political Science Association]], the [[Midwest Political Science Association]], the [[International Studies Association]] and the [[Cyber Intelligence Network]].<ref name="northeasternryanmaness"/>
